title: souther
body:
[b]Souther[/b] ([b]サウザー[/b]), also romanized as [b]Thouzer[/b], is one of the antagonists from [[Hokuto no Ken]].

Souther represents the "Star of Leadership" (将星, Shosei), which rules over the other Nanto stars. His fighting style is Nanto Ho-oh Ken (南斗鳳凰拳, "South Star Phoenix Fist"), the strongest of the Nanto Seiken, which is a purely offensive style with no defensive stance. He is immune to most of the techniques of the Hokuto Shinken because of his "Emperor's Armor," a congenital condition called [i]situs inversus totalis[/i] which completely reverses the position of his internal organs and pressure points.

Souther was orphaned as an infant and was raised by the previous Ho-oh Ken successor, Ohgai, who trained him during childhood. During his final training lesson, Souther unwillingly killed his sensei, who intentionally allowed himself to be killed by the former as a part of the succession test. Traumatized by the event, Souther disavowed all feelings of love and compassion. After the Nuclear War, he takes on the title of Holy Emperor (聖帝, Seitei) and enslaves children with his army in order to construct the [[seitei jujiryou|Holy Cross Pyramid]], a shrine to his deceased sensei.

h4. Known moves

* 極星十字拳 ([i]Kyoukusei Juuji Ken[/i])
** An attack which leaves a cross-shaped wound on the opponent's chest.

* 天翔十字鳳 ([i][[Tenshou Juuji Hou]][/i])
** The style's ultimate technique. Souther takes a stance with his arms held out evenly, like a cross. As the name suggests, it is launched into a powerful aerial attack. This technique makes the user so light and graceful that he can glide over any physical attack.

title: nissan_skyline_r32
body:
The eighth generation of the [[Nissan Skyline]], produced from 1989 to 1993. 

The R32 was the third Skyline to have a [[Nissan Skyline GT-R|GT-R]] variant, reviving the badge 16 years after the [[Nissan skyline c110|C110]] GT-R's discontinuation. Designed for Group A racing in particular, the GT-R version debuted shortly after the base model and was sold for another year after the base R32 had been phased out.

This generation of the Skyline is notable for several appearances in racing anime and games. Several R32s were featured in [[Initial D]], where they are driven by [[Nakazato Takeshi]], Shimamura Eikichi, and Houjou Rin. In [[Wangan Midnight]] R32s are driven by [[Akikawa Reina]], Hiramoto Kouichi, and Tomoya.

title: h_p_lovecraft
body:
[b]Howard Phillips Lovecraft[/b] (August 20, 1890 – March 15, 1937) — known as [b]H. P. Lovecraft[/b] — was an American author of horror, fantasy and [[science fiction]], especially the subgenre known as weird fiction.

Lovecraft's guiding aesthetic and philosophical principle was what he termed "cosmicism" or "cosmic horror", the idea that life is incomprehensible to human minds and that the universe is fundamentally inimical to the interests of humankind. As such, his stories express a profound indifference to human beliefs and affairs. He is best known for his [[Cthulhu Mythos]] story cycle and the [[Necronomicon]], a fictional grimoire of magical rites and forbidden lore.

Although Lovecraft's readership was limited during his lifetime, his reputation has grown over the decades, and he is now regarded as one of the most influential horror writers of the 20th century. His stories have also been adapted into many plays, films and games.

title: nissan_skyline_c110
body:
The fourth generation of the [[Nissan Skyline]], produced from 1972-1977. Notable for it's [[muscle car]]-styled design, inspired by popular American cars of the time.

Like it's [[nissan skyline c10|predecessor]], the C110 had a [[nissan Skyline GT-R|GT-R]] performance variant. Launched in September 1972, this generation's GT-R version was only produced for 7 months before being discontinued as the impact of the 1973 oil crisis caused sports cars to fall out of favor in Japan. A total of 197 C110 GT-Rs were produced during it's short run, and the GT-R badge as a whole was discontinued until the [[nissan skyline r32|R32]]'s GT-R variant launched 16 years later.

title: muscle_car
body:
A high performance and potent [[car]], usually American, sometimes Australian, British or South African. Distinctive characteristics include a large, heavy frame similar to a mid-size family sedan, a huge V8 engine with at least 4 liters (244 CID) of displacement, a gearbox with extremely tight ratios, an interior with enough room for 4 people, and a price that is much lower than an European simile. Due to their poor handling and their fabulous acceleration, they are best suited for straight-line drag racing.

Examples of muscle cars include the AMC Machine, the [[Chevrolet Chevelle]], the Ford Torino, and the 2010 [[Dodge Challenger]].

Similar in concept is the pony car, which is basically a smaller, lighter muscle car, such as the [[Ford Mustang]], the 1970 [[Dodge Challenger]], or the [[Chevrolet Camaro]]. While not often considered muscle cars, many Japanese cars in the 70s (such as the [[Nissan Skyline C110]], [[Toyota Celica A20]], and [[Mitsubishi Galant GTO]]) featured styling that made them resemble compact muscle cars.

title: incan
body:
The [b]Inca Empire[/b], or [b]Inka Empire[/b] (Quechua: [i]Tawantinsuyu[/i]), was the largest empire in the pre-Columbian American Continent. 

The administrative, political and military center of the empire was located in Cusco in modern-day [[Peru]]. 

The Inca civilization arose from the highlands of Peru sometime in the early 13th century. 

From 1438 to 1533, the Incas used a variety of methods, from conquest to peaceful assimilation, to incorporate a large portion of western South America, centered on the Andean mountain ranges, including large parts of modern Ecuador, Peru, western and south central Bolivia, northwest Argentina, north and north-central Chile, and southern Colombia into a state comparable to the historical empires of the Old World.

The empire ended in 1533 with the arrival of the European [[spain|Spaniards]], who conquered it.

title: dodge_challenger_(3rd_generation)
body:
The third generation [[Dodge Challenger]]. Debuted in 2007, this generation was notable for reviving the nameplate after over 20 years of dormancy, with a highly popular design directly inspired by the [[dodge_challenger_(1st_generation)|original version]]. Participated in several American motorsport series during it's production, including [[NASCAR]] and Trans Am.

The model was ultimately discontinued in 2023, as part of [[Dodge (company)|]] (and the Stellantis Group as a whole) moving towards a fully electric lineup. No direct successor to the Challenger was announced at the time of it's discontinuation, instead the [[Dodge Charger]] received a new, muscle car-styled electric coupe to replace the long-standing sedan.

An Ultimate [[Digimon (creature)|]] that is the result of the Jogress between [[Darkdramon]] and [[BanchoLeomon]]. According to the Central Dogma of the Digital World, 'Chaosmon' is the codename for Digimon that 'should not exist'. Its left arm, the Darkdra Arm, is equipped with the Gigastick Cannon (explaining the Arm Cannon tag), while its Banchou Arm is equipped with the BAN-TYO Blade. The Digimoji on the Blade say 'KAOSU', transcribed as 'CHAOS', which hints at its name.

Another variant exists, called Chaosmon: Valdur Arm, which is the Jogress between [[Valdurmon]] and [[BanchoLeomon]]. There is also [[UltimateChaosmon]], a Jogress between all of [[Darkdramon]], [[BanchoLeomon]], [[Valdurmon]] and [[Sleipmon]].

title: titan_(submersible)
body:
An experimental tourism [[submarine|submersible]] built by OceanGate, designed to take rich customers to the [[shipwreck|wreckage]] of the [[rms titanic|Titanic]]. It used a cylindrical design with a carbon fiber body, had a capacity of five people, even an onboard [[toilet|lavatory]], and was controlled by a [[Logitech]] F710 [[game controller|gaming controller.]] Its design was heavily criticized by submarine experts and was largely made of off-the-shelf components (such as using construction pipes for ballast).

On [[2023 titan submersible incident|June 18, 2023]], 740 kilometers off the coast of Newfoundland, [[Canada]], its surface ship lost contact with the Titan 1 hour & 45 minutes into the dive, but didn't call for help until 8 hours later, after the sub was supposed to return. Multiple government agencies from the [[United States]] and [[Canada]] were involved in the massive search spanning four days and  over 25000 square kilometers. By June 22, the date when the emergency oxygen was predicted to be depleted, an ROV had located debris which was confirmed to be part of the sub, and later had been determined that the vessel had imploded. All 5 people onboard, including OceanGate's CEO have been declared dead. Subsequent investigations revealed the vessel was practically doomed from the start, due to poor design and ignorance by the company's CEO, including him firing an expert for telling him his vessel was not seaworthy and previously saying things that essentially amounted to "screw safety."

As a "Doom Guardian":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/3/39/Immortal.png], his outfit is mostly the same, save for a black shirt under his jacket. His arm is seen undergoing a demonic transformation, turning it ash black, with his eyes glowing yellow.

title: exorcist_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male priest (dungeon and fighter)|male Priest]]. Also known as the Hyperion or Draconid.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/b/bd/ExorcistPortrait.png] has longer brown hair, wearing Eastern-themed red and white robes. He is seen using both his prayer beads and a large, golden battle axe as weapons.

As a "Neo Exorcist":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/0/04/Neo-_Exorcist_Artwork.png], his hair is worn loose and ragged, with his beard graying. He's now seen topless, exposing a black Eastern dragon tattoo along his left arm and shoulder. title: leomon
body:
Leomon is a [[muscular]] lion-man with orange fur, yellow mane, yellow fur on its legs and the tip of its tail, [[blue eyes]], black nose and mouth, five fingers on its hands and feet, black claws, black ear tips, and scars on its arms, left foot, and the left side of its face. Its ears are on top of its head. 

It wears a golden earring on its left ear, a [[collar]] with with a blue [[gem]] in the middle and multiple red teeth around it, [[black pants]] with yellow cords forming multiple "X" on its side, a black belt with a square metallic buckle on its waist, three others on its left arm, another in its left hand, and another in the pantleg. It carries its [[sword]] in the back on its belt.

It is called the "King of Beasts", as well as the "Noble Hero". While most [[Digimon]] are ferocious, it possesses a strong will and a heart of justice, and has defeated a great number of fiendish [[Digimon]]. Also, it is a rival to the "Digimon Hunter" [[Orgemon]], who runs the whole gamut of destruction. Its tough flesh, tempered well by daily training, can endure any attack, and since it chokes the life out of the opponent with its quick attacks, 

Leomon can be said to be an outstanding Combat Species. It carries a sentient magical [[sword]] called "Beast Sword" (獅子王丸 Shishiou-maru?, lit. "Lion King") on its waist. Also, it is matchless friends with [[Garudamon]], who possesses the same will. [[Cyclonemon]]'s right eye was crushed by Leomon.

h4. External links

title: hadouken
body:
The Hadouken (波動拳, "Surge Fist") is a special attack that originated in the classic [[Capcom]] fighting video game series [[Street Fighter]]. The practitioner thrusts his or her palms forward, sending a surge of spirit energy (or ki) flying towards the opponent. It is referred to colloquially as the "Fireball", even though most versions of the Hadouken do not involve the use of fire.

Not to be confused with the [[Kamehameha (dragon ball)|]]. The Hadouken is a ball rather than a beam, though the Shinkuu Hadouken in the VS. series of fighting games is a beam possibly as an homage and that Ryu probably wouldn't be able to keep up with the other fighters if it wasn't a beam.

The "Hadouken" was inspired by the [[Wave Motion Gun]] ("Hadou hou") from the legendary [[Uchuu Senkan Yamato]] science fiction series from the 70s.

title: steyr_hs_.50
body:
The [b]Steyr HS .50[/b] is a single-shot, [[bolt action]] [b][[anti-materiel_rifle|anti-materiel]] [[sniper rifle|sniper]] [[rifle]][/b], chambered in .50 BMG. It has no built-in magazine. Each round has to be loaded directly into the ejection port and is pushed into the chamber by the bolt. The fluted barrel is cold hammer-forged and has an effective range of up to 1,500 m. It has an adjustable [[bipod]], a [[muzzle device]] that reduces recoil significantly, and a Picatinny rail for the installation of various optics.

The original Steyr HS-50 was designed by Heinrich Fortmeier, on behalf of Steyr Arms. Unlicensed variants of the HS. 50 include the AM-50 Sayyad produced by Iran and the Golan S-01 produced by Syria. The HS .460 variant is chambered in .460 Steyr [[ammunition|cartridge]] instead.

title: gensou_suikoden_iv
body:
The fourth game in the [i][[Gensou Suikoden]][/i] series. It is the first prequel game of the series, taking place 150 years before [i][[Gensou Suikoden I]][/i]. It takes place among the Island Nations, to the south of [i]Gensou Suikoden I[/i]'s Scarlet Moon Empire, during an invasion by the Kooluk Empire which was engineered by "Merchant of Death" Graham Cray, and follows exiled Gaien Knight [[Lazlo (suikoden)|]]. Lazlo, following the usual [i]Gensou Suikoden[/i] formula, becomes the host of a True Rune (the cursed Rune of Punishment) and the leader of the rebel military. Due to its location, travel and major battles in the game are carried out by ship instead of on land. It also has the fewest returning characters of any game in the series, with four characters from previous games who were already established as immortal being present.

Due to its simplified gameplay (especially the reduction of party size from the traditional six to only four), annoyingly frequent random battles, and a story that never really lives up to its potential, [i]Gensou Suikoden IV[/i] is widely considered the worst in the series.

title: jeane_(suikoden)
body:
Jeane (ジーン) is a recurring character in the [[Gensou Suikoden]] series, having appeared in every game except the alternate universe [[Gensou Suikoden Tierkreis]]. She usually serves multiple roles once recruited, including magic rune merchant, army unit commander, and playable party member. In addition, she is usually the most prominent (but never the sole) provider of fan service in the series, making her a fan favorite.

[spoiler][[Gensou Suikoden V]] intimates that Jeane is thousands or even tens of thousands of years old, making her likely the oldest character in the series, True Runes excepted. How she accomplishes this, as well as detail about her personal history and motivations, is unknown.[/spoiler]

title: bell_jar
body:
A [i]bell jar[/i], also known as a [i]cloche[/i] or [i]display dome[/i], is a bell-shaped vessel made usually of glass and sometimes of plastic and designed to cover objects or contain gases or a vacuum.  These objects have various purposes.  In a household setting, they were normally used as a protective dust cover for the object covered by it.  In a lab setting, they were used to trap gasses or vacuums within the container, in this setting they're specifically referred to as a [i]bell jar[/i].  In an agricultural setting, they were used to cover outdoor plants to protect them from frost, in this setting they're specifically referred to as a [i]cloche[/i].

A bell jar may or may not have a knob at the top to serve as a handle when picking it up.

For danbooru however, fainting refers to merely to the act of becoming limp and collapsing.

Also applies to a character that has fainted, though not to be confused with [[sleeping]].

title: camel_clutch
body:
A [[wrestling]] move where the wrestler sits on the back of his opponent, who is face down on the mat, and places the arm or, more commonly, both arms of the opponent on his thighs. The wrestler then reaches around the opponent's head and applies a chinlock and then leans back and pulls the opponent's head and torso.

A camel clutch can also refer simply to a rear chinlock while seated on the back of an opponent, without placing the arms on the thighs. The move was invented by Gory Guerrero in Mexico, where it was called la de a caballo (Horse-mounting choke), but got its more common name from Ed Farhat, who wrestled as "The Sheik" and used it as his finisher. The late [[WWE]] Hall of Famer The Iron Sheik also used it as well. 

A standing variation of the camel clutch is also used, with this variation popularized by Scott Steiner in the late 1990s as he used it as his finisher dubbed the "Steiner Recliner". Steiner's nephew, WWE wrestler Bron Breakker, also uses the Recliner as one of his finishing moves.  

Current [[All Elite Wrestling]] wrestler Miro also uses the camel clutch (which he formerly named as "The Accolade" during his past WWE run as Rusev) which he currently calls as the "Game Over".

title: platoon
body:
[i]The first casualty of war is innocence...-[/i] Main tagline.

[i][b]Platoon[/b][/i] is a 1986 American anti-war film written and directed by Oliver Stone, starring an ensemble of several actors lead by Tom Berenger, [[Willem Dafoe]], and [[Charlie Sheen]]. 

It is the first film of a trilogy of Vietnam War films directed by Stone, followed by [i][b]Born on the Fourth of July[/b][/i] (1989) and [i][b]Heaven & Earth[/b][/i] (1993).

Stone wrote the screenplay based upon his own brutal, terrible and traumatic personal experiences as a [[united states|U.S.]] [[soldier|infantryman]] in the [[Vietnam War]], to counter the falsely heroic and pro-militaristic vision of the war portrayed in John Wayne's [i][b]The Green Berets[/b][/i] (1968). 

Platoon was the first Hollywood film to be written and directed by an actual veteran of the Vietnam War.

Platoon won the Academy Award for Best Picture of 1986; it also won Best Director for Oliver Stone, as well as Best Sound Mixing and Best Film Editing. In 1998, the American Film Institute placed Platoon at #83 in their "AFI's 100 Years... 100 Movies" poll.

title: sope_(food)
body:
A [b]sope[/b] ([[spanish_text|Spanish]] pronunciation: [ˈso.pe]) is a traditional [[mexico|Mexican]] dish consisting of a fried masa base with savory toppings. Also known as [b]picadita[/b] (in Tierra Caliente, Guerrero), it originates in the central and southern parts of [[Mexico]], where it was sometimes first known as [b]pellizcadas[/b]. It is an [[antojito]] or Mexican fast food, which at first sight looks like an unusually thick [[tortilla]] with vegetables and meat toppings.

The masa base is fried with pinched sides and topped with refried [[beans]], crumbled cheese, [[lettuce]], [[onions]], red or green [[sauce]] and [[sour cream]]. Sometimes other ingredients (mostly different types of [[meat]]s) are also added to create different tastes and styles.

title: battle_of_caen
body:
[b]The Battle for Caen[/b] (June to August 1944) is the name given to fighting between the [[united_kingdom|British]] Second Army and the [[germany|German]] Panzergruppe West in [[World War II]] for control of the city of Caen and its vicinity during the larger [[invasion_of_normandy|Battle of Normandy]] in occupied [[France]]. 

The battles followed [b]Operation Neptune[/b], the Allied landings on the French coast on 6 June 1944 ([[D-Day]]) and ended with a decisive and costly Allied [[victory]]. However, the city of Caen ended up completely destroyed with several French civilian casualties as a consequence.

title: sherman_firefly
body:
The [b]Sherman Firefly[/b] was a [[tank]] used by the [[United Kingdom]] in [[World War II]] that traded mobility for fire power. 

It was based on the ubiquitous US [[M4 Sherman]] tank, but fitted with the powerful 3-inch (76.2 mm) caliber British 17-pounder anti-tank gun as its main weapon to counter the heavy armor used by Germany's [[Wehrmacht]] in the European theater. 

Originally conceived as a stopgap until future more powerful British tank designs came into service, the Sherman Firefly became the most common vehicle mounting the 17-pounder in the war. While the weapon proved effective against the heavier [[germany|German]] tanks, it was difficult to use due to the excess of fumes produced by firing the gun in the cramped turret of the vehicle, which greatly impaired visibility during battle.

title: legend_of_chaoshan_heroes
body:
Overview: The original material of this meme was shot in 2010, and it was just a funny video shot by a group of young people in the Chaoshan area of Guangdong, China. However, due to poor production, it unexpectedly became popular online. After the 「例のアレ」meme into China, this material was discovered by【美男(BiliBili ID)】, named it【潮汕英豪传（Legend of Chaoshan Heroes）】, and tried to learn from Niconico's creative style to develop it into a subculture similar to 【Gachimuchi】or【Inm】. 

【潮汕英豪传】has developed for the second time since 2018. Many of the main authors are Chaoshan natives (including the organizer of Chaoshan Touhou Only), who can easily understand the video content across the dialect barrier. This helps the development of this meme has been closer to subculture rather than only be a otomad material, and can build a set of world views and stories based on the original video. Therefore, the【潮汕英豪传】 can be said to be one of the few 「例のアレ」memes from  China，Or it can be called Chinese style「例のアレ」memes

The company is located in Jieyang City, Guangdong Province, China. Most of the actors in the film use local language, this dialect is called Chaozhou dialect(潮州話/潮汕話). In Southeast Asia, British colonists often heard the language spoken by immigrant laborers from the Chaoshan region. After they transliterated this language into English, they called it Teochew dialect.

title: qrow_branwen
body:
Qrow Branwen is a supporting character in [[RWBY]], a 3DCG series produced by Rooster Teeth.

Qrow is [[Raven Branwen]]'s brother and uncle of [[Ruby Rose]] and [[Yang Xiao Long]]. He is an experienced Huntsman and an ally of the main characters. He has a gloomy, pessimistic personality and a drinking problem.

h4. Abilities

Qrow is a highly experienced and skilled fighter. He wields Harbinger, a large sword that can transform into a scythe and incorporates a built-in shotgun. His semblance (special ability) causes bad luck to others around him. [spoiler]He is also capable of transforming into a crow.[/spoiler]

h4. Physical characteristics

Qrow is a 6'1" tall man with a gangly build and narrow, angular face. He has unkempt graying [[black hair]], narrow [[red eyes]], and sparse [[facial hair|stubble]] along his jaw. He tends to stand with a slight slouch. His voice is raspy.

h4. Attire

Qrow wears a white and grey shirt with black cuffs and lapels, black pants, black dress shoes and a tattered red [[cape]]. He wears a crooked [[cross necklace]] around his neck, a black band around his right wrist and [[ring]]s on several fingers.

[b]Unicorn[/b] is a sentient transformable [[alien]] robot who is a member of the [i]Transformables[/i], a group of brave and powerful transformers who were created by prince [[Zacek]] to protect planet [[Zuyua]] and the Zuyua people.

Unicorn's body is yellow, green and silver; he has a very powerful arm cannon on its left arm unit and a spiked mace on its right hand unit, as well as a potent diamond driller on the top of his head unit (hence the name). His alternate mode is an advanced combat subterranean vehicle.
 
Unicorn is one of the strongest Transformables and serves as the weapons and combat expert of the group.

title: camellia
body:
A flower growing in evergreen shrubs native to Asia, especially in Japan, China, and Korea.

In art, these flowers are usually red, but sometimes white or pink. They have a bright yellow center that sticks up and often only have a single layer of petals. They grow on a bush, though they are more often seen as cut flowers.

The actual flower has more differences between varieties, particularly in the number of petals, but the "Camellia Japonica" variety is the one most commonly seen in anime-centric art.

title: dry_suit
body:
A dry suit is a [[diving suit]] similar to a [[jumpsuit]] designed to protect the wearer from exposure underwater. 

In contrast to a [[wetsuit]], which allows water through, a dry suit is meant to maintain a watertight environment for the wearer. As such, a dry suit is baggier and is often not skin-tight. It insulates the wearer better than a wetsuit and so is more suitable for cold or deep water, not so much for beach recreation.

title: gift_bag
body:
Either a small [[bag]] made out of fabric that is tied at the top with a ribbon, or a colored paper bag with stringed loops at the top for holding. The bag will contain a [[gift]] for one person to give to another as a surprise.

Don't confuse this with a [[sack]], often associated with [[Christmas]] and [[Santa Claus]]. A sack is one large bag that can carry multiple wrapped gifts, whereas this is a single bag with a gift inside it. An example with both a gift bag and a sack clearly present is post #374610.

h4.See also

* [[gift box]]
* [[Christmas stocking]]

title: standard_diving_dress
body:
The standard diving dress is a type of [[diving suit]] which incorporates a hard copper [[diving helmet]] and a [[dry suit]], oftentimes including an [[oxygen tank]] and [[gloves]]. It was specifically designed to be used for deep water work which required the user to be underwater for long periods of time.

Note that the helmet of the standard diving dress is specifically made of metal and leaves only a small porthole to see through, often obscuring the diver's face. If the [[diving helmet]] is a glass dome, such as in post #5849345, do not include this tag.

title: power_rack
body: A power rack, also called a squat rack, is a piece of [[weightlifting]] equipment designed to be used as a mechanical spotter for free weight [[barbell]] exercises, most often [[squatting|squats]]. The most common design is of four vertical bars in the shape of an upright rectangle with two lower bars, called the bar catches, connecting two of them near the bottom to catch a falling barbell. An alternative design uses only two vertical bars, but maintains the two bar catches. Most often found in [[gym]]s.

title: tasc-01-scf_logan
body:
A [[mecha]] from the [[Choujikuu Kidan Southern Cross]] [[science fiction]] anime series from the 80s.

The [b]TASC-01-SCF "Logan"[/b] is a small, fast and agile aerospace variable mecha used by the [[TASC]] to defend [[planet Glorie]].

The Logan is armed with a triple barreled ion cannon on its nose and a small energy [[gunpod]]. It can also carry a limited amount of [[missile]]s. Standard units are painted blue while ace units are painted golden and orange.

Its mecha form resembles a [[VF-1]] [[variable fighter]] from [[Macross]] in [[Gerwalk]] mode.

The Logan is [[TASC]] ace [[pilot]] [[Mary Angel]]'s mecha of choice.

title: mary_angel
body:
A main character from [[choujikuu_kidan_southern_cross|The Super Dimension Cavalry Southern Cross]] [[mecha]] anime series from the 80s.

[b]Mary Angel[/b] is a member of the [[TASC]] (Tactics Armored Space Corps), an aerospace combat unit used for defense of the human colonies from [[planet Glorie]].

She is a very professional (and somewhat arrogant) mecha fighter ace. Her robots of choice are the [[tasc-01-scf_logan|Logan]] and the [[Auroran]].

Her name in the [[ROBOTECH]] western adaptation was changed to [b]Marie Crystal[/b].

Mary's character design was based in the American female rockstar "Joan Jett":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joan_Jett .

title: decepticon
body:
A fictional faction of evil sentient [[alien]] [[robot]]s from the planet [[Cybertron]]. They are usually the main antagonists in the fictional universe of [[Transformers]]. 

These villainous transforming [[robot]]s can take many forms, and have many different origins and stories across the numerous different Transformers media, but in almost all incarnations, they are led by [[Megatron]]. They are typically represented by the purple facial insignia they all wear. Primarily, [b]Decepticons[/b] have red eyes, while their enemy [[Autobot]]s have blue eyes. They are usually known for their air power, especially since many of them turn into [[aircraft]]. Decepticons often turn into [[military]] vehicles, construction vehicles, and even smaller-than-human-sized objects. 

In [[Japan]]'s version of the franchise, the Decepticons are called [b]Destron[/b] or [b]Deathtron[/b] (Japanese: デストロン Desutoron). The one exception to this naming convention is Car Robots, where the sub-group referred to as "Decepticons" in the Robots in Disguise adaptation, is known in Japan as the Combatrons (the Japanese name of the G1 subgroup known as the Combaticons). The overall name of the Robots in Disguise villain faction is [b]Destronger[/b]. However, the Japanese version of Transformers Animated uses Decepticon (ディセプティコン). 

The title Decepticons is derived from the word [i]"deception"[/i] in the English language.

title: enchantress_(dota)
body:
Aiushtha appears to be an innocent, carefree creature of the woods, and while this is certainly true, it is hardly the sum of her story. She well understands the suffering of the natural world. She has wandered far, and fared through forests bright and drear, in every clime and every season, gathering friends, sharing news, bringing laughter and healing wherever she goes. For in worlds wracked by war, forests are leveled for the building of ships and siege engines; and even in places of peace, the woods are stripped for the building of homes, and as fuel for countless hearths. Aiushtha hears the pleas of the small creatures, the furtive folk who need green shade and a leafy canopy to thrive. She lends her ears to those who have no other listeners. She carries their stories from the wood to the world, believing that her own good cheer is a kind of Enchantment, that can itself fulfill the promise of a verdant future.

Voiced by Gin Hammond.

title: couch
body:
A large upholstered piece of furniture designed to seat several people. Also known as a "sofa."

The smallest type of couch, one that seats two people, is referred to as a "loveseat."  A couch with a 90 degree bend in it is a "sectional couch," and as the name suggests is composed of several separate sections.

There may be some overlap between a small "loveseat" type couch and a large [[easy chair]]. When in doubt, just tag them as a couch.

[[chaise_longue|Chaise longues]] (French for "long chair") are also called couches, commonly used as the stereotypical "psychiatrist's couch."

h4. See also

* [[Bench]]
* [[Chair]]
** [[Easy Chair]]

title: flat_screen_tv
body:
A flat-screen [[television]], or more accurately a flat-panel television, is a television set with a thickness usually under 10 cm (~4 in.).  This is opposed to [[crt|cathode-ray tube televisions]] or rear-projection televisions whose designs required rather thick housing.

This tag is specifically for flat-panel tvs, which the term "flat-screen tv" is used interchangeably with today.  It should not be used for rear-projection tvs or flat-screen cathode-ray tube tvs, which were particularly common before LCD and similar technologies become the dominate technology used for televisions.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia - Flat-panel display":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flat-panel_display]
